reply.question: 3. Does the app declare the purpose of data collection and use?

answer.full_answer: Yes, the app declares the purpose of data collection and use in order to provide mental health support, resources, and connection to NSW & ACT Emergency Service members.

reply.analysis: The privacy policy explicitly states that the purpose of the service is to provide mental health support, resources, and connection to specific emergency service members. This aligns with declaring the purpose of data collection and use.
reply.reference: The purpose of this Service is to provide mental health support, resources and connection to NSW & ACT Emergency Service members. URL: https://emergeandsee.disciplemedia.com/onboarding_documents

reply.question: 4. Can the user opt out of data collection or delete data?

answer.full_answer: Yes, the user can opt out of data collection or delete data.

reply.analysis: The privacy policy mentions that the user's decision to disclose personal information is entirely voluntary, and they can withdraw consent for the processing of personal data. Additionally, the policy states that users have the right to request the deletion of their data and that data will be securely and permanently deleted under certain conditions.
reply.reference: Your decision to disclose your personal information to Us is entirely voluntary. If you do not provide the personal data necessary, or withdraw your consent for the processing of your personal data, you may not be able to access or use the App. We will securely and permanently delete your personal information when there is no justification for its further retention, or you have asked Us to delete it. URL: https://emergeandsee.disciplemedia.com/onboarding_documents
